# PR boundary and muP

- Do not add sparse imports to PR1 `minicpm_sala.py`.
- Do not change muP residual scaling (`scale_depth / sqrt(num_hidden_layers)`) or embed/logit scales.
- Do not alter kernel contracts (e.g. `infllmv2_attn_stage1` tier-2 keys in v/cu_seqlens_v slot).
- Keep `supported_dtypes = [torch.bfloat16]` and KV cache bf16/auto only.
- Sparse fixes go under `pr2/` only unless explicitly PR1-shared (tests, docs).